y, and the third documents the rise of relativity and quantum theory in the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAesthetics. 0aRationalism. 0aSciencexMathematical models. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 4aGeneral Science. 4aHistory Of Science.  aAesthetic appreciation.  aAesthetic experience.  aAesthetic judgment.  aAesthetic pleasure.  aAesthetic qualities.  aAesthetic theories.  aAesthetics.  aArt appreciation.  aArt interpretation.  aArt.  aP. A. M. Dirac.  aStructure of Scientific Revolutions.  aThomas S. Kuhn.  aaesthetic judgement.  aaesthetic theory.  aaesthetics in science.  aaesthetics.  aempirical performance.  ahistory of science.  aphilosophical aesthetics.  aphilosophy aesthetics.  aphilosophy of science.  arationalism.  astructure of scientific theories.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172864840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501728648423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501728648/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles